title: Matt Gonzalez Supports Chris Daly
author: d6politics
description:
Re-Elect Chris Daly! www.daly06.com

Matt Gonzalez, former president of the San Francisco Board of Supervisors speaks in support of Supervisor Chris Daly's re-election at a rally on October 28th, 2006. Filmed at the 16th and Mission BART plaza.

"The only reason Rob Black is a viable candidate is because we suffer from amnesia."

"When we go and campaign for Chris Daly, we are trying to reverse this amnesia, but we're also character witnesses for him."

title: Chris Daly - Whose City? Our City!
author: d6politics
description:
Re-Elect Chris Daly! www.daly06.com

San Francisco Supervisor Chris Daly psyches up a crowd of supporters at a rally on October 28, 2006. 

Chris talks about the Mission, recent campaign mailers sent by Daly's moneyed opponents, and quality of life of San Francisco.

"If we don't care of the least of us, we will not take care of the issues they care about, unless we 
totally gentrify this city and make it into a Downtown France, if you will. But that ain't gunna happen, because there is political fight left in us. This is our city." -Daly on condo-owners and their favorite candidate Rob Black

"The Realtors can be pissed off at me because I stand up for tenants at every turn. And they can send a mailer, they can send another, they can send a third- they can spend a million dollars in this campaign if they want- but they cannot buy the District 6 Supervisor seat. They cannot buy San Francisco because San Francisco is not for sale. This city does not belong to them. This is not their city, this is our city." - Labor and homeless activist Chris Daly tells it like it is!

Filmed at 16th and Mission BART plaza.

title: Power Party Political Commercial
author: talawolf
description:
In Government class, we hosted a mock election. This mock election included three political parties, The Republicans, The Democrats, and a third party.

I was nominated as the head of the third party. A Fascist party. We called ourselves the Power Party.

We only had a couple thousands of dollars (of fake money), less in the comparison to the millions of dollars the Democrats and Republicans. We only had five members in our party, in comparison to the 12 that the other two parties had. We basically got all the votes we could by walking around wearing black sunglasses and ties, and being persistant on people. We blew all the money we had making small simple black and white posters and making this commercial.

However, I had won the great debate we had.

And I had also won the election. It was the first time in the history of the Mock Elections held at my school that a third party had won.

Our video became a hit. Heavily inspired by the movie 'Fight Club'. It really seemed to fit with our party.

description: from the Throwing Muses 'Gut Pageant' reunion show/ party in Boston in May, 2000. filmed by Dave Johnson. The original studio version of 'Hysterical Bending' was recorded around the time of Hips and Makers, and can be found on a 1994 various artists cd called "Just Say Roe".

title: Throwing Muses - Hillbilly (live)
author: matt600
description: sound check performance from the Throwing Muses reunion show/ party in Boston in May 2000 known as Gut Pageant. filmed by Dave Johnson. There's an excellent studio version of 'Hillbilly' that was recorded during the 'University' sessions in 1993, but it didn't make it onto that album. Eventually it ended up on an obscure soundtrack and a UK various artists cd. Over time, as word of 'Hillbilly''s greatness spread, it turned into something of a cult favorite among fans. So much so, it was one of the most requested TM songs prior to this reunion show. I believe this is the first time the band played it in front of an audience.

title: 2001 November NYC Ground Zero trip
author: matt1996
description: I traveled to NYC on business in Nov 2001, almost excatly two months to the day after the attacks.  We came out of Penn Station and learned a plane had just crashed in Queens.  It was the first plane crash since 9/11--it was accidental but everyone was really on edge and it made for a completely surreal day in Manhattan.  We visited ground zero and got some stark footage of damage to buildings around the WTC, layers of dust still caked everywhere.  Businesses still being cleaned up.

title: Throwing Muses - Fish
author: matt600
description:
Throwing Muses' first promo video, filmed sometime around early 1986. Kristin, Tanya and David were about 19 at the time. The video is based around a live performance of 'Fish', so this version of the song is unique to the video.

There are 2 studio recordings of 'Fish' that have been released. The first was produced by Gary Smith in 1985 and can be found on the 'In A Doghouse' 2-cd set. There's also a later one produced by Gil Norton, and possibly recorded during the sessions for the 'Chains Changed' ep, that is on a 1987 4AD Records compilation called 'Lonely Is An Eyesore', and has not been released elsewhere yet.

title: Apocalypse Rising Trailer
author: Matt6908
description:
They year is 2088, and civilization is quiet. 4 teenagers are wandering around ancient Mayan ruins, when the find hieroglyphics on the wall. So they translate and it says the world will end in at the very beginning of the year 2089. So they tell the government, but they just ignore them. So on new years eve right when the clock strikes 12:01, all hell breaks loose. Meteor showers, fires, explosions, unexplained deaths, etc. Basically Armageddon. Eventually one of the meteors bring a disease that plagues everyone on earth, except for the 4 teenagers. They were under hiding. When they come out, they find the world literally destroyed, and everyone on earth are zombies. So they have to combat them all, while trying to avoid the on coming meteor showers, fires, explosions, etc. I'm not going to give away the end. NOTE: This is just the trailer

Visit HollywoodNHouse.com for my video information.
